  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`StatusAppNavBar` has been designed in a way that it comes with three sections:\r\n\r\n1. A chat button section\r\n2. A dynamic community button section\r\n3. A static section for additional buttons\r\n\r\nWhen the list of community buttons grows, so that the space in which all buttons live shrink.\r\nBecause of that, section 3) anchors to the bottom of the navbar as soon as the growth of section 2) causes the entire navbar content to be bigger than the available space, and section 2) becomes scrollable.\r\n\r\nTo make this work, there are some `height` calculations happening here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/d690a0c505d04d92b40d6e744526ad3a6f6acf03/src/StatusQ/Layout/StatusAppNavBar.qml#L23-L29\r\n\r\nHere:\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/d690a0c505d04d92b40d6e744526ad3a6f6acf03/src/StatusQ/Layout/StatusAppNavBar.qml#L74-L84\r\n\r\nAnd here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/d690a0c505d04d92b40d6e744526ad3a6f6acf03/src/StatusQ/Layout/StatusAppNavBar.qml#L121-L133\r\n\r\nAnd lastly retriggered, whenever the section 2) changes in size:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/d690a0c505d04d92b40d6e744526ad3a6f6acf03/src/StatusQ/Layout/StatusAppNavBar.qml#L93-L97\r\n\r\nHowever, what the component doesn't take into account at the moment, is when the available space of the entire navbar changes. For example when users resize their window. It breaks the UI when the list of community buttons is big enough.\r\n\r\nWe should fix that and see if we can recalculate the component's height whenever the app window height changes.",
